      <div class="bio-section fade-up">
        <div class="bio-label">About</div>
        <p>Chelle Dorn is the founder and CEO of Forge Partners, Inc. and the architect of the Stress Test™ and Strength Index™ diagnostic system. With over 20 years of hands-on organizational change management experience at enterprises including Roche, Genentech, Chevron, State Farm, and Warner Bros., she built Forge Partners on a single conviction: execution failure is structural before it is operational. The Stress Test™ and Strength Index™ were not theorized in a classroom — they were built in boardrooms, pressure-tested across global transformations affecting hundreds of thousands of people, and refined until they produced a score a leadership team could actually act on.</p>
        <p>Her credential stack is the precise combination the market is now demanding — change management, executive coaching, Industrial &amp; Organizational (I-O) psychology, project management, and adult education — held simultaneously, not sequentially. This is the foundation of Forge's methodology, and the reason no competitor can replicate it. Chelle serves as the firm's lead diagnostic architect, primary client advisor, and the certifying authority for every practitioner who carries the Forge methodology into an engagement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-section fade-up">
        <div class="bio-label">Discipline Architecture</div>
        <div class="discipline-wheel">
          <!-- Row 1 -->
          <div class="discipline-cell">
            <div class="disc-glyph">⬡</div>
            <div class="disc-name">Change Management</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">20 years leading enterprise transformation. PROSCI certified. The operating backbone of every Forge engagement.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell center-cell">
            <div class="disc-center-label">Integrated in</div>
            <div class="disc-center-name">The Stress Test™ &amp; Strength Index™</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell">
            <div class="disc-glyph">◎</div>
            <div class="disc-name">I-O Psychology</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">The academic foundation of the diagnostic. Brings behavioral science rigor to organizational assessment.</div>
          </div>
          <!-- Row 2 -->
          <div class="discipline-cell">
            <div class="disc-glyph">◈</div>
            <div class="disc-name">Executive Coaching</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">C-suite fluency. Works at the level of the buyer, translating structural data into leadership action.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell center-cell">
            <div class="disc-center-label">Resulting in</div>
            <div class="disc-center-name">A quantified score leaders can act on, track, and move</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell">
            <div class="disc-glyph">◻</div>
            <div class="disc-name">Project Management</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">Structured delivery discipline. ITIL Foundation certified. Ensures every engagement is rigorous and repeatable.</div>
          </div>
          <!-- Row 3 — full width spanning all 3 cols -->
          <div class="discipline-cell" style="grid-column:1/2">
            <div class="disc-glyph">▷</div>
            <div class="disc-name">Adult Education</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">Powers the certification curriculum. Practitioners trained to a transferable, PMP-equivalent standard.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell center-cell" style="grid-column:2/3">
            <div class="disc-center-label">Delivered through</div>
            <div class="disc-center-name">A certified practitioner network that scales the methodology</div>
          </div>
          <div class="discipline-cell" style="grid-column:3/4">
            <div class="disc-glyph">◉</div>
            <div class="disc-name">AI Transformation</div>
            <div class="disc-desc">Organizational readiness diagnostics for AI adoption — the fastest-growing engagement category in the firm.</div>
          </div>
